Introduction

CRAXY is a four-member girl group under 1EVEL Enm consisting of Woo-Ah, Karin, Hyejin, and Swan. They debuted on March 3, 2020, with the full-length album "My Universe". Originally a five-member group, it was announced in July of 2023 that member ChaeY would be leaving the group and the group would continue as four.

Prior to debuting, all of the members were part of the pre-debut team Wish Girls alongside two other trainees (Yujin and Hana) who didn't debut in CRAXY. As Wish Girls, they released three digital singles: "Wish For You", "Yours Is Mine", and "Wish Mas".
